 A fruit seller buys a dozen of banana at Rs.X. He sells 1 banana at Rs.Y. Write a program to determine the profit or loss in Rs. for the fruitseller.
Input format:
Input consists of 2 floating point numbers
The first input corresponds to the total cost(X)
The second input corresponds to the sold cost(Y)
Output format:
Print "Profit or Loss" with Rupees.
Sample Input:
60
4
Sample Output:
Loss : Rs.12.00


answer:

total_cost = float(input("Enter the total cost (Rs.): "))
sold_cost = float(input("Enter the sold cost per banana (Rs.): "))
cost_per_banana = total_cost / 12
if sold_cost > cost_per_banana:
    profit = (sold_cost - cost_per_banana) * 12
    print(f"Profit : Rs.{profit:.2f}")
else:
    loss = (cost_per_banana - sold_cost) * 12
    print(f"Loss : Rs.{loss:.2f}")

output:
Enter the total cost (Rs.):  50
Enter the sold cost per banana (Rs.):  10
Profit : Rs.70.00
